<paragraph blockId="6.[136,347,1238,1264]" box="[136,347,1238,1264]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<heading bold="true" box="[136,347,1238,1264]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,347,1238,1264]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Identification 
<taxonomicName authority="Schott (1832: 18)" authorityName="Schott" authorityPageNumber="18" authorityYear="1832" box="[305,347,1238,1264]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Colocasia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">key</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="key">
<key lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">1. Plants with stolons; stem short to tuberous and decumbent, or rhizomatous; with multiple adaxial buds in each leaf axil; spadix with sterile appendix or not; staminodes between ovaries many to abundant ...................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">- Plants without stolons or side-tubers; stem cylindrical, erect; a single adaxial bud in each leaf axil; spadix always with sterile appendix; staminodes between ovaries few or absent........................................................................................................................6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
2. Sterile appendix long (up to ca. 
<quantity box="[518,580,1427,1448]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
,&gt; 2x length of male zone), thick, diam. up to 
<quantity box="[1024,1091,1427,1448]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
at base (wider than male zone) ......... ........................................................................................................................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hayata" authorityYear="1919" box="[1320,1451,1455,1477]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Colocasia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="formosana">
<emphasis box="[1320,1451,1455,1477]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. formosana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" box="[136,1451,1484,1506]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1484,1506]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">- Sterile appendix short and slender, much reduced, or completely absent ..........................................................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
3. Sterile appendix short (length 
<quantity box="[506,575,1513,1535]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="3.5">3.5 cm</quantity>
, equal to male zone), slender conical, diam. 
<quantity box="[1011,1067,1513,1535]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
at base (more narrow than male zone); underside of leaf blade surface pilose, main and primary lateral veins pubescent; petiole and peduncle pubescent .......................... ..................................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1451,1571,1592]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Colocasia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="menglaensis">
<emphasis box="[1304,1451,1571,1592]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. menglaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">- Sterile appendix absent or much reduced; underside of leaf blade pubescent over whole surface, or not; petiole and peduncle not pubescent ............................................................................................................................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
4. Plant stout, petiole maximum 
<quantity box="[502,561,1657,1679]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="55.0">55 cm</quantity>
long; stem short (&lt;
<quantity box="[752,800,1657,1678]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[862,910,1657,1678]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="3.0">3 cm</quantity>
diam.; sub-globose); inflorescence appears with leaves; peduncle little shorter than petiole .......................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li &amp; Long" authorityYear="1999" box="[1277,1450,1686,1707]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Colocasia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gaoligongensis">
<emphasis box="[1277,1450,1686,1707]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. gaoligongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
- Plant tall, 50–100+ cm long; stem sub-globose to elongate, decumbent, minimum 
<quantity box="[1028,1077,1715,1736]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
long; inflorescences appear after leaf emergence; peduncle much shorter than petiole.................................................................................................................................5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
5. Blade cordate-ovate, upper surface waxy, not glossy green, often with dark purple patches; interprimary veins very prominent on underside of mature blade; sterile appendix absent (a much reduced vestige, apiculate, &lt;
<quantity box="[1115,1160,1801,1823]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="1.0">1cm</quantity>
); staminodes between ovaries abundant, with flask shape and discoid apex............................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1451,1830,1851]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Colocasia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis box="[1304,1451,1830,1851]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
- Blade cordate-sagittate, overall elongate-triangular with deep sinus, upper surface not waxy (wettable), glossy green, without purple patches; interprimary veins inconspicuous to slightly raised on underside of mature leaf; sterile appendix completely absent; staminodes between ovaries abundant, obovate with rounded apex ................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Long &amp; Liu" authorityYear="2001" box="[1333,1450,1916,1938]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Colocasia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lihengiae">
<emphasis box="[1333,1450,1916,1938]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. lihengiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
6. Leaf blade oblong-ovate, posterior lobes narrow and rounded; underside of blade pubescent over whole surface, including primary veins; peduncle cylindrical........................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName box="[1311,1451,1974,1995]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Colocasia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kachinensis">
<emphasis box="[1311,1451,1974,1995]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">C. kachinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" box="[136,1451,2003,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,2003,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">- Leaf blade cordate-ovate; posterior lobes broad and rounded; no parts pubescent; peduncle three-angled ......................................7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,1307,2082]" lastBlockId="7.[136,1452,159,325]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
7. Plant very large, petiole 
<quantity box="[455,567,2032,2053]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="115.0" valueMax="140.0" valueMin="90.0">90–140 cm</quantity>
; stem erect or nearly erect, 
<quantity box="[845,966,2031,2053]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.275" metricValueMax="1.35" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="127.5" valueMax="135.0" valueMin="120.0">120–135 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1032,1129,2032,2053]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="15.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="12.0">12–18 cm</quantity>
diam.; leaf blade with distinctly indented sinus, main vein and primary lateral veins purple, lamina “membranous”; peduncle green or purple; spathe ca. 
<quantity box="[1390,1451,2060,2082]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="33.0">33 cm</quantity>
long, spathe blade yellow with purple margin, almost erect or sometimes reflexing at anthesis; spadix ca. 
<quantity box="[1216,1275,159,181]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="30.0">30 cm</quantity>
long, little shorter than spathe ............................................................................................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Long &amp; Li" authorityYear="2000" box="[1361,1450,188,209]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Colocasia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gongii">
<emphasis box="[1361,1450,188,209]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. gongii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[136,1452,159,325]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
- Moderate sized plant, petiole up to 
<quantity box="[553,627,217,238]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="120.0">120 cm</quantity>
, stem erect or decumbent with erect apex, up to 
<quantity box="[1096,1155,217,238]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="14.0">14 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1217,1283,216,238]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="5.5">5.5 cm</quantity>
diam.; leaf blade with shallow sinus, main vein and primary lateral veins green; lamina thick, rubbery, smooth on underside; peduncle green; spathe up to 
<quantity box="[266,326,274,296]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="19.0">19 cm</quantity>
long, spathe blade yellow without purple margin, strongly reflexed at anthesis; spadix 
<quantity box="[1167,1263,274,296]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="cm" value="12.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="10.0">10–14 cm</quantity>
long, much shorter than spathe ..................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="P. J. Matthews, V. D. Nguyen, Q. Fang &amp; C. L. Long" authorityYear="2022" box="[1315,1451,303,324]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Colocasia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spongifolia">
<emphasis box="[1315,1451,303,324]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. spongifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</key>
